properties.description: Two brothers, Max and Arthur Schwartz, were the children of Eastern European immigrants that came from a long line of dairy farmers. They grew up on a 40 acre dairy farm founded at the turn of the century in the Middle Village area of Queens. Their father started the farm by purchasing 7 cows from the west side of Manhattan, which he walked back to Queens by crossing the newly constructed Williamsburg Bridge.
